# Showbook Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** July 5, 2026

Thank you for using Showbook.

Your privacy is important. Showbook has been designed to work primarily on your device without requiring an account or transmitting your personal data.

## Information We Collect

Showbook does **not** collect, store, or transmit your personal information.

The app does not require you to create an account and does not collect your name, email address, phone number, or other personal information.

## Access to Your Photo Library

Showbook requests permission to access your photo library solely to display, organize, browse, and manage the photos and videos you choose to make available to the app.

The app may also read photo metadata (such as EXIF information), including information like capture date, camera model, lens information, image dimensions, and other embedded metadata necessary for the app's functionality.

Your photos and their metadata remain on your device. They are not uploaded to the developer or shared with third parties.

## Data Storage

All app data is stored locally on your device unless Apple's operating system performs encrypted device backups according to your personal iCloud settings.

The developer does not operate any servers that receive your photos or personal information.

## Analytics and Tracking

Showbook does not use analytics services, advertising SDKs, or tracking technologies.

The app does not track your activity across apps or websites.

## Third-Party Services

Showbook does not use third-party services that collect personal information for analytics, advertising, or marketing purposes.

## Children's Privacy

Showbook does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updates will be published together with a revised "Last updated" date.

